03:44.268 --> 03:47.792
be fairly simple, and others may not agree with it. For a number of years, there simply wasn't much market for fantasy, 
and everybody knew it, so nobody wrote it. And Del Rey Books decided to take a plunge and get into fantasy in a big way. They

04:01.133 --> 04:03.234
tried to get good new authors. They tried to get old ones to convert over and do serious, well-written fantasy. I was one 
of the ones that shifted over from science fiction to fantasy. And apparently it worked, because now most of the

04:14.144 --> 04:21.191
best-selling fantasy is with this one publisher, Del Rey Books. And I conjecture that they took the plunge, and it 
worked. When fantasy was given the same push that science fiction was, it had the same success and now is being carried

04:26.892 --> 04:38.927
on, perhaps, on momentum beyond the science fiction levels. Now, most people will tell you there's a deep 
philosophical aspect that somehow people crave fantasy when they don't crave science fiction. But I don't see that the

04:47.338 --> 04:53.946
world has changed that much in five years to make People suddenly crave a genre that they didn't want before. I think, 
again, the answer has to be in the commercial aspect, in the push, in the advertising, in the promotion that they give the

04:57.886 --> 05:06.516
novels. I think people just didn't know about fantasy before. As I said, this is not an answer most people will give you, 
and I'm not sure whether it's accurate. It's just my theory. How did you decide to write fantasy, to take the plunge in

05:19.190 --> 05:23.595
your career? It was almost entirely coincidental. It's a long history. I'll try to digest this down. I've had a good deal 
of trouble in the genres because I stand up for my rights. One publisher was sending me, well, they sent me statements of

05:41.098 --> 05:47.786
account that were simply not true. They were wrong. And I knew they were wrong. demanding a correct statement and 
