06:03.700 --> 06:06.925
And this happened to be Ballantine Books. What changed in six years was that the administration there changed. And new 
editors came in that weren't interested in blacklisting me. They happened to know that I had had the right of it. But by

06:19.162 --> 06:23.749
that time, in that six years, I had gotten in with other publishers. And I don't know if you're familiar with this. 
There's an option clause in most contracts that say, in general, we reserve the right to publish or to approve and have

06:27.415 --> 06:41.096
the first purchase rights on this author's next piece of fiction. If they buy it, then they put the clause in the next 
contract, and so on, so that you're locked into one publisher. I was locked into Avon Books on science fiction. Avon is

06:52.657 --> 06:56.821
where I went after Ballantine Books blacklisted me. With the new administration at Ballantine Books, I wanted to try 
them out. I wanted to see if they really had changed and do a novel for them, but I couldn't legally do science fiction. So I

07:09.394 --> 07:11.697
said, well, supposing I try fantasy? I haven't done any. I don't know if it'll work, but if you're willing... It happened 
that Lester Del Rey was the fantasy editor. I knew him. I'd met him. I liked him. I like his kind of editing. So on that

07:21.326 --> 07:25.091
basis, I got into fantasy. Again, it was a commercial decision. And then when I tried it, I discovered I liked it. And then 
it went from there. What was your first fantasy effort? Okay, the first, the modern one, okay, the very first one I did and

07:37.188 --> 07:44.839
put into print was a novel called Hassan. And that took some years to get into print. I wrote it back in 1968. It was an 
adaptation of an Arabian Nights fantasy tale that I admired. And I did some research and brought it up and fleshed it out

07:56.381 --> 08:01.608
and made it into a novel. It was published serially in Fantastic Magazine back in 1968 or 1969, 1970, somewhere in there. 
Couldn't get book publication. But more recently, when I say with the option complication or Ballantine books, I

08:15.380 --> 08:27.892
simply started a whole new framework for fantasy. And that's when I did a spell for chameleon. And this is what really 
