fantasy. Now, I don't say I like this situation, but I have to live with it. I can't sell outside of the genre. It has 
nothing to do with how good a writer I may be. If I listen to my fans within the genre, they think I'm one of the best. But

14:25.674 --> 14:28.417
outside, they couldn't care less. They're just not interested. So if I'm going to write at all, I have to write within the 
genre. So wrestling with this reality, and I pride myself on being able to face reality, realized that unless I wanted to

14:42.796 --> 14:51.606
do 100% fantasy, I would have to return and find a way to do science fiction and still satisfy myself. But when I thought it 
out, I realized that the boundaries of both science fiction and fantasy are very tenuous. You can call almost anything,

15:01.878 --> 15:09.246
one genre or the other, if you phrase it correctly. So in effect, What I did was stretch the boundaries of science fiction 
so that they would include the mainstream material that I really wanted to work on. And as a result, I have now sold to Avon

15:22.689 --> 15:36.985
Books a five novel science fiction series that is really a mainstream series closed to science fiction It's not that it 
doesn't have the science fiction trappings. It's very hard science, and nobody would ever confuse it. But that the

15:46.546 --> 15:49.730
message in it, the theme, it's a mainstream theme. I'm dealing with the problems of the world and possible solutions to 
