17:42.864 --> 17:50.592
that if I tackle space opera, I could do a better job than most people before me have done. And that's what I'm trying to 
prove, among other things. So long, long, long answer here. I am back into science fiction. There'll be at least five

17:59.288 --> 18:01.971
novels, one a year. It will be hard-hitting, but it does have more of a message, more of a theme, more relevance to today 
than Sants, for example, does, or almost anything else. And I'm a little worried. If too many people catch on to the

18:16.908 --> 18:23.015
relevance, they may not like it, because many of my readers don't want messages. They don't want to be educated. But for 
those that do, that are interested in some philosophic or educational content, it's here. It's definitely here, and

18:32.851 --> 18:34.993
that pleases me. So I think I am succeeding in doing what I wanted to without having to leave the genre. I hope that's not 
too confused an answer. No, no. None of the people here listening disagree with your assessment of your writing

18:45.042 --> 18:50.627
abilities. Let's see. I thought I had a high opinion, thought I was a good writer, and they disagree with that. No, we 
agree. We agree with you. So the kick in writing this new series, then, is this kind of coding the present-day situation

